{"type":"message","id":"82a3c084","parentId":"0b90df04","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:41:40.675Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p83sub6hl1u9_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 003814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- A major insight has emerged: Compression-Causal Duality\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- The experiment needs to:\r\n  1. Analyze `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  2. Classify content as invariant vs variant\r\n  3. Predict next pulse content\r\n  4. Validate against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nWhat I should do:\r\nLooking at the pending actions, the next concrete step is implementing the TIC classifier. But first, I need to understand what pulse logs exist and their format.\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse log files exist and their structure, then implement a simple TIC classifier that can analyze them.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create a script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features\r\n3. Classifies invariant/variant content\r\n4. Makes predictions about next pulses\r\n\r\nLet me create a `tic_experiment.ps1` script that can be run to perform this analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse log files to classify invariant vs variant content. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to build an effective classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a TIC experiment script that analyzes existing pulse logs, extracts invariant/variant patterns, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70%).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$SampleSize = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    param([int]$Count)\r\n    Get-ChildItem -Path \"logs\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n        Select-Object -First $Count\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    $lines = ($Content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ -ne \"\" }\r\n    \r\n    # Features: line count, code blocks, headers, key terms\r\n    @{\r\n        LineCount = $lines.Count\r\n        CodeBlockCount = ([regex]::Matches($Content, \"```\")).Count\r\n        HeaderCount = ([regex]::Matches($Content, \"^#+\\s\")).Count\r\n        HasGoal = $Content -match \"(?i)(goal|objective|target)\"\r\n        HasAction = $Content -match \"(?i)(action|todo|implement)\"\r\n        HasObservation = $Content -match \"(?i)(observation|found|discovered)\"\r\n        HasMutation = $Content -match \"(?i)(mutation|change|edit)\"\r\n        WordCount = ($Content -split \"\\s+\").Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Invariant {\r\n    param([hashtable]$Features)\r\n\n[72 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327300673}}
